 should be implemented. Stop applications and services that do not need to be used on the SCADA network.\n	the services which are not needed to be used continuously in SCADA network such as e-mail, internet access, remote access services should be stopped, and their access should be denied. Do not rely on SCADA Protocols to secure your network. Security should not only be implemented with SCADA protocols; many SCADA protocols cannot provide a real security. Follow the safety definitions recommended by the device and system manufacturers for their products.\n	Older devices do not have such configurations, but newer devices have security applications (SSL access, User Management, Log management, etc.). * If security configurations are supported according to the status of your assets, apply these configurations with support from your supplier. Take control of the accounts and devices that can be used as backdoor.\n	Many manufacturers may have accounts on their devices to provide private access, and these accounts must be found, and their access rights must be checked. Place intrusion detection and prevention systems (IDS / IPS) inside and outside of your network and provide 24/7 monitoring of the network.\n	With IDS systems, monitor the transactions of your SCADA network continuously so that abnormal or malicious transactions can be detected as soon as possible. Perform periodical technical inspections for your SCADA network, your corporate network, and other connected networks.\n	System and Network Administrators should regularly perform network and system checks using the required technical control software. Perform inspections at central and remote sites to measure and ensure the reliability of physical access.\n	Check that the physical environments in which all devices that make up the SCADA network are located are closed to unauthorized access. Train or build your team to analyze and detect attacks on the SCADA network.\n	With a team of experts in SCADA networks, ensure that threats are recognized and prevented as soon as possible. Identify Cyber Security duties, responsibilities, and user authorizations clearly and perceptibly.\n	The whole organization needs to be informed about cyber security, duties should be identified, and accesses should be configured. Document network architecture and identify your systems which hold critical or valuable information.\n	Always keep your documentation up-to-date in terms of visibility and knowledge management of the entire SCADA network. Create an attentive and sustainable risk management process.\n	Create an effective security and risk management process that the entire organization can follow. Create an in-depth protection strategy for your network (defense-in-depth principle).\n	Review all access and authorization rules. Build your protection strategy in depth as a Physical-Network-End point. Define cyber security requirements.\n	Create your rules and procedures with a cyber security program. Define duties and responsibilities in your organization and follow your procedures regularly. Create an effective configuration management process.\n	Create a configuration management process to keep your network and device configurations constantly up to date and under control. Perform periodical internal audits.\n	Control your security with internal audits as a part of your cyber security procedures. Create system backups and recovery plans.\n	Create backup and recovery plans to compensate for potential system and service loss as soon as possible. As top management identify performance criteria and responsible persons for Cyber Security.\n	Define your expectations from cyber security in line with the objectives of your organization. Establish internal rules for the security of the SCADA network and systems, and increase the level of knowledge of the organization regarding the subject through internal trainings.\n	Organize internal trainings to constantly keep your organization\'s level of knowledge and cyber security procedures up-to-date and maintain awareness.\n \n', NULL, '21-steps-to-provide-cyber-security-of-scada-networks1', '21 Steps to Provide Cyber Security of SCADA Networks', 'PUBLISHED', '0', '2019-09-09 05:15:57', '2020-01-31 07:13:04', NULL, '[]', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'en', '[]'),
(8, 2, 14, 'internet-of-things', 'LoRaWAN-Satellite Solutions', 'LoRaWAN-Satellite Solutions', 'The Internet of Things (IoT) relies on the Internet as its name. While many devices may use mobile networks, which are terrestrial-based,', 'The Internet of Things (IoT) relies on the Internet as its name. While many devices may use mobile networks, which are terrestrial-based, business-centric applications often need the greater reach and reliability offered by the satellite technology. Using LoRaWAN and Satellite Communications together, you can quickly and easily collect data from your hard-to-reach areas and make your business more efficient.\nConnected Remote Assets\n\nMonitoring assets, communicating with remote facilities and managing unmanned, remote sites can all be done through the power of connected technology. Without satellite technology, none of this would be possible.To the average observer, terrestrial mobile networks appear sufficient to cover this need, but this is not the case in all areas of the world.\n\nImproved Mobile Connectivity\n\nMobile networks break down in many parts of the world, and satellite technology is necessary for the connected devices used to track vehicles in this way to actually function properly and continue to convey the data they are designed to convey.\n\nImproved Reliability and Speed\n\nSatellite technology allows more reliability for IoT devices and services than land-based networks alone. For applications that demand always-on connectivity, satellite integration is essential. Similarly, speed is becoming increasingly important to IoT developers and the people who use their services.\n\nUse Cases\nIn Remote sites without GSM coverage or expensive connection costs;\n\nEnergy tracking,\nCold Supply Chain tracking,\nTransmission Lines tracking,\nVehicle and Personnel tracking,\nAgriculture and Forests tracking,\nSecurity applications,\nWi-Fi\nFor more information, please get in contact with us! (Click Here for Mail)', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\N9AQ3zM5L4VTqChVFdKO.jpg', 'lorawan-satellite-solutions', 'LoRaWAN-Satellite Solutions', 'PUBLISHED', '0', '2019-09-09 05:15:57', '2020-01-31 10:11:47', 'LoRaWAN-Satellite Solutions', '[]', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'en', '[]'),
