be created in PI Vision ™; so that your users can be used as a phone, tablet or computer on any platform. These display panels / screens can transmit in the form of information, in a graphical form that facilitates information and shaping.\r\n\r\n\r\nEnerji kullanımını izlemek ve enerji girişiminin etkisini değerlendirmek için haftalık veya aylık raporlar üretmesi gereken kullanıcılar, ihtiyaç duydukları verileri PI DataLink ile Microsoft® Excel® raporlarına götürebilirler.\r\nMicrosoft PowerBI veya SQL Server Raporlama Servisleri gibi araçlarla standart etkileşimli raporlar oluşturulabilir ve veriler PI Integrator for Business Analytics ile bu raporlara / araçlara beslenebilir.\r\nEnerji manzaranıza gerçek zamanlı görünürlük sağlamak için PI Vision ™ ‘da enerji gösterge panoları veya işlem göstergeleri oluşturulabilir; bu sayede kullanıcılarınız herhangi bir platformda bir telefon, tablet veya bilgisayar olarak kullanılabilir. Bu gösterge panoları / ekranları, bir bilgi biçiminde, bilgi ve şekil vermeyi kolaylaştıran bir grafik biçiminde iletebilir.\r\n \r\n\r\n**Benefits of PI System in Energy Sector**\r\nEnergy costs are major operational costs for most industries. Understanding your energy use is very important to process improvement and efficiency, as well as to embrace an energy-conscious culture in your organization. With better visibility in energy use, it is easier to understand how operational practices affect energy consumption. But reducing energy consumption is not only good for the bottom line. And reducing energy consumption can minimize an organization\'s carbon footprint, reduce overall social impacts, and maintain reputation of company as being responsible for environment.\r\nFor example, Anglo American Platinum used the PI System to provide visibility of power consumption and to enable various energy management initiatives. They made the data visible in the organization and achieved 1% reduction in electrical power consumption. This reduction partially provided real-time feedback to end users, allowing them to see the impact of the changes they made in the process. Carnegie Melon University started a project to monitor facilities with PI System and Microsoft Azure Machine Learning. They concluded that they could reduce their energy costs by 20% by implementing their solution. Similarly, MOL Group, an international Oil and Gas company, uses the PI System to produce EnPIs to monitor energy data. They expect 2% reduction of annual steam and fuel gas consumption as well as 20,000 tons / year CO2 reduction, and to have a share of € 3,5 million per year with reduced operational costs.\r\n\r\n\r\nAs a result, any reduction in energy consumption can result in significant savings. Companies in various industries can benefit significantly from energy analysis. The PI System can help your company base on energy consumption, accelerate process improvement, increase efficiency, and provide visibility in impact process solutions on energy initiative objectives. Companies wishing to benefit from the PI System for energy optimization projects can try to adopt the strategies outlined in this presentation by contacting KONTROLMATIK and getting information about AF studies (mail link).', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\EQtQXKeuGiU4FGY6uz73.jpg', 'osisoft-pi-system-monitoring-and-managing-energys', 'OSIsoft PI Sistem: Enerjiyi İzlemek ve Yönetmek', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-10 13:32:36', '2020-01-30 06:08:59', 'OSIsoft PI System: Monitoring and Managing Energy', '[\"Nesnelerin \\u0130nterneti\",\"Otomasyon\",\"Technologies\"]', NULL, 'en', ''),
(16, 2, 3, 'asset-management', 'Convert Your Operational Data into Value with OSIsoft PI System', 'Convert Your Operational Data into Value with OSIsoft PI System', 'What is OSIsoft PI System? Companies are struggling to collect and manage data from operational assets using today\'s technology.', 'What is OSIsoft PI System? Companies are struggling to collect and manage data from operational assets using today\'s technology.\n\nIf you are one of these companies, you are familiar with the following data moving from system to system with a spaghetti model;\n\nThe OSIsoft PI System is an expert in complete simplification of this picture. It assists you in all your processes to obtain, archive, manage and analyze huge amounts of sensor data. PI System provides organization-wide solutions for collecting, storing, analyzing data and sending it to users.\nThink of the PI System as a tool for providing the data to users and applications that need the data from sensors. This is basically a three-step process; Data Collection, Analysis, Integration.\n\n1- Data Capture / Collection\n\nReal-time data streams start from DCS, PLC, SCADA, HAVAC, OLEDB, SAO or another source. OSIsoft has developed over 400 standard interfaces that support industry-standard protocols such as OPC, Modbus, RDBMS and can connect to the systems of major providers. Manual data entries are also supported. This does not only save tremendous time, but also significantly reduces risk (bad data, etc.). The interfaces are intelligent: with automatic discovery of data sources, they have important details such as data buffering, filtering of bad data, and so on. These details help you monitor clean and reliable data.\n\n2- Data Analysis Process After data collection, it should be stored and prepared for analysis. This is a big job that most databases cannot handle. Remember: Industrial sensor data are fast. 1-100hz is not an extraordinary data speed and the operators who use it need the information on time.\nThe PI System stores data instantly on arrival and provides it to users or applications in real time. Yes, this is a real-time system and so you can see the PI System at many control centers around the world.\nHowever, providing only real-time data will not be sufficient to meet the requirements of Industry 4.0. For this reason, the PI System can do things that make your work quite easy, such as calculations (simple KPIs and very complex mathematical formulas), unit conversion, labeling events, sending notifications.\nWhen you want to make historical analysis, you can query the data from 10-20 years back in just seconds. All data is warm and usable - the fact that there is no waiting and complex archiving is a great thing. Imagine you are dealing with data that\'s big enough to get lost in. The OSIsoft PI System does this without any complaints. Because the PI System is optimized to provide industry strength performance and reliability.\n\n3- Manage Your Data Decide how you want to analyze all this data and leave the rest to the PI System. Note that sensor flow naming conventions are useless. An article by OSIsoft summarizes this problem as follows;\n\nTypically, only a few users for the control system naming convention can take full advantage of the value placed in the semantic field. Others spend their valuable time trying to find and integrate “accurate” operational data for analysis. As a result, operational data often remain dark, untouched, inadequate or forgotten.\nWhat happens if we add these strange technical names to a metadata model (such as hierarchy)? This is exactly what the PI System does: Label names depend on real world assets such as transformers, pumps and reactors. Then, you can browse a large amount of data in the business view and also create asset templates for easy system configuration. Each template cannot contain standards just like calculations, units of measurement and other useful things. In fact, thanks to this system, it became much easier to work with data. It became possible to compare one pump to another and standardize sensor data models on equal assets.\n\nInterpretation of big data requires automatic configuration. This is especially true for sensor data. In an industrial environment, we always deal with analyzing specific events such as batch times, starts, stops, etc. These periods include stories and information to help you improve the processes. However, it is very difficult to find and compare when it is left unstructured. The OSIsoft PI System automatically flags these events. You can then easily compare various groups or analyze only what causes a downtime.\n\nAs a Result, Your Data is stored on your PI Server for many years from your systems at the desired accuracy and speed. You can organize your data by assets and events and use the PI Analytics options such as PI ACE or PI Notifications. Your data will always be securely accessible for use by any person or system. When you are ready to use your data, you will be given different options. PI Clients provides a graphical, intuitive and easy way to visualize your data with products provided by OSIsoft. PI System Access provides different methods to access data and integrate them into business intelligence systems, corporate reporting software, and customized applications using standard protocols such as OLEDB or Web Services.\n', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\y17BMtpdJopSpZZZ0A3W.jpg', 'convert-your-operational-data-into-value-with-osisoft-pi-system', 'Convert Your Operational Data into Value with OSIsoft PI System', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-12 09:54:13', '2020-01-31 06:46:28', 'Convert Your Operational Data into Value with OSIsoft PI System', '[]', NULL, 'en', ''),
