(21, 2, 3, 'asset-management', 'Asset Performance Management', 'Asset Performance Management', 'The success of asset-intensive companies (electricity generation, transmission, distribution, mining, transportation, etc.) depends on the success of critical assets. It is crucial to have these assets at disposal. A number of costs occur (Procurement, Operation, Maintenance) to keep assets i', 'The success of asset-intensive companies (electricity generation, transmission, distribution, mining, transportation, etc.) depends on the success of critical assets. It is crucial to have these assets at disposal. A number of costs occur (Procurement, Operation, Maintenance) to keep assets in working order and to provide the expected benefit from them each time. The main purpose of Asset Management is to keep assets running continuously at optimum cost.\n\nWhether it is public or private sector; a good asset management strategy should be established to meet stakeholder expectations and maximize product/service value without approaching assets as physical, financial, human or “abstract”. Asset Management includes coordinated and optimized planning of assets and asset systems, asset selection, acquisition / development, use, maintenance, and final disposal or replacement. Analysis regarding integration and optimization of asset management has provided significant performance benefits to the present since the 1990s by identifying key business processes, compliance activities and system integration features.\n\nBenefits of Asset Management:\n\nThe tangible results of risk-based, life-cycled asset management have been increasingly proven in the world.\n\nThese are;\nThe harmonious and healthy operation of processes, resources and operations. Ensuring transparent control of what is done and when it is done. Better understanding and using data and information to make information based and consistent decisions. Improved planning. Consistent, prioritized and controllable risk management. Accordance and coordination of existing initiatives, including competence development. Increased value participation of the workforce including leadership, communication and interdisciplinary teamwork. Asset Management is standardized with ISO 55000. ISO 55000 consists of 3 standards in series.\n\nThese are;\n\nISO 55000 provides an overview of asset management and standard terms and definitions. ISO 55001 is the specification for an integrated, effective management system for asset management. ISO 55002 provides guidance for the implementation of such a management system. Looking at the entire life cycle of the asset, operation and maintenance is the longest phase, and most of the costs occur in this phase. Therefore, optimizing this phase provides the greatest return. And Asset Performance Management addresses this phase.\nABB Solution for Asset Performance Management: Asset Health Center\nABB offers leading software and deep field expertise to the world\'s most asset-intensive industries in energy, utilities and mining, from plant level to regional network level and global wide operations.\nWith Asset Health Center, you can track your valuable assets with online and offline information, instant and historical analysis; create trend analyzes, create predictive and prioritized maintenance plans, and manage the entire asset life cycle from purchasing to decommissioning.\n\nBenefits of Asset Health Center:\n\nIncreased Asset Reliability: Provides identification of assets in advance which present potential risks and have deterioration risks. Thus, by reducing unexpected faults, all kinds of material and security threats that may be caused by these faults are eliminated. Asset Visibility: By getting informed about the latest status of your valuable assets, you are provided with access to your assets continuously and information exchange. Reducing costs with condition-based maintenance: Predictive maintenance or prioritization of maintenance is provided based on the performance status of your assets. Longer product life and reduced initial purchase costs with healthy maintenance: A healthier operation and product management is provided by prioritizing the maintenance of your assets that need maintenance. Compliance and reporting can be done quickly: You can quickly access the list and status of your assets and access reports and outputs as quickly as possible.\n\n', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\FwEE8B1wd2N4whvpQXCV.jpg', 'asset-performance-management', 'Asset Performance Management', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-12 11:11:17', '2020-01-31 06:42:33', 'Asset Performance Management', '[]', NULL, 'en', ''),
