(28, 2, 18, 'network', 'Cyber Security in Industrial Control Systems (ICS)', 'Cyber Security in Industrial Control Systems (ICS)', 'Industrial systems have high value due to their economic and vital infrastru', 'Industrial systems have high value due to their economic and vital infrastructures. Energy generation-distribution, water distribution, ventilation etc. systems, as critical infrastructure; are quite important in supporting daily life. In addition, there are lots of personal and corporate information recorded in the databases and information systems of the corporations that provide service.\nToday, cyber attacks against high-value Industrial Control Systems have become more frequent globally and the necessity of taking precautions in this regard has been understood once again. As a result of the attacks on these systems, cities and even countries have been blacked out and personal and corporate information have been stolen.\nThe figures of the research conducted by Cambridge University in England are quite remarkable; according to this research, a large-scale cyber attack against England could result in an economic loss of 12-85 Billion Pounds, hundreds of thousands of households experiencing power loss, trains and airlines stopping, and possible casualties. (The original report can be found here)\n** How can a Distribution Network Cyber Attack occur? **\n	Providing access to an on-premise computer user through a hoax e-mail or malicious software. By this means, identification of the servers that hold important data with user\'s computer and the user.\n	Possession of equipment inventory, user accounts and passwords due to low security on servers.\n	Providing access to SCADA servers.\n	Corruption of system configuration through SCADA software.\n	Shutting down the disks of SCADA servers and making them inoperative.\n	Opening the relays in the Electricity distribution network with the command given.\n	Making the software of RTU / IED devices as unusable as possible.\n	Ok, can such an attack be prevented?\nIn order to prevent possible cyber attacks on control systems;\nIt should be designed in inside to outside manner, network segmentation should be done and access to whole network should be prevented even if an attack occurs. It should be possible to detect industrial network traffic with anomalies. It should be possible to prevent unauthorized operations on the IED/RTU, smart end devices. It should be possible to prevent known malware from infecting Industrial Systems (OT). It should be possible to prevent Known/Unknown malware from infecting Information Systems (IT). User authentication and authorization must be controllable on all systems. All access must be logged and recorded.\n	To ensure complete security, security should be ensured across your entire network with planning; by reviewing your entire security infrastructure and performing risk analysis.\nKontrolmatik produces customized solutions for you for end-to-end cyber security solutions in your Industrial Control Systems (ICS) by making your systems\' risk assessment and analyzing your control system networks, so that you can protect your industrial systems.\n(sales@kontrolmatik.com)\n', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\5HBbDix3wGqdxb9ayuPy.png', 'cyber-security-in-industrial-control-systems-ics', 'Cyber Security in Industrial Control Systems (ICS)', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-12 09:44:47', '2020-01-31 07:05:36', 'Cyber Security in Industrial Control Systems (ICS)', '[]', NULL, 'en', '[\"Cyber Security\"]'),
(29, 2, 6, 'dcs', 'Kontrolmatik - ETİ Maden 75t / h Fluidized Bed Boiler', 'Kontrolmatik - ETİ Maden 75t / h Fluidized Bed Boiler', 'With 800xA DCS system prepared by Kontrolmatik, independent turbine, ESP, Compressor and Flue gas measurement systems have been integrated to each other and the project has been completed in a way to ensure the best system efficiency.', 'With 800xA DCS system prepared by Kontrolmatik, independent turbine, ESP, Compressor and Flue gas measurement systems have been integrated to each other and the project has been completed in a way to ensure the best system efficiency.\nThe new generation, small size coal-fired power plants provide a clean, green and safe energy production from cheap powder coal. These plants have all the technological infrastructure and equipment that large thermal power plants have.\n\nThe purpose is,\nTo provide the steam that the process needs. To generate the energy Required by the Process and Reducing Production Costs Result\nThe internal requirement is designed to be fully redundant via 2 transformers. Diesel generator busbar is created for Automatic take over when power is off and emergency loads are fed through this busbar. To prevent harmonics, all Motors, pumps and Fans in the site are controlled by Low Harmonic drivers. The system is designed using ABB 800XA DCS system. In this way, CPU SCADA and all controls can be done from a single point. SIL3 applications have been performed for system security. All drives are controlled via Profibus. This reduces both the number of cables and the points of failure in the system. With the ESP system installed, flue gas is released to the nature at minimum level. By using OPC, Modbus and Profibus communication systems, all the auxiliary systems of the boiler were communicated and integrated operation was provided in a single system.\n\nAdvantages of Kontrolmatik,\nWith 800xA DCS system prepared by Kontrolmatik, independent turbine, ESP, Compressor and Flue gas measurement systems have been integrated to each other and the project has been completed in a way to ensure the best system efficiency. With the system built, the turbine and boiler operate in an integrated manner. 75t / h steam produced at 43 Bar 450° C runs a 10 MW turbine and the steam leaving the turbine meets the steam demand of the process. SIL3 is designed in accordance with the safety system considering the problems that may occur in the boiler.\n\nEti Maden,\nEti Maden Isletmeleri General Directorate is an international Organization operating in the fields of Mining, Metallurgy and Chemicals with its Bandırma Boron and Acid Factories, Kırka Boron, Emet Boron, Bigadiç Boron Operations Directorates and Bandırma Logistics Unit, as well as Overseas Representatives and Subsidiaries.\n\nEti Maden Isletmeleri General Directorate, which is formed to evaluate all kinds of mineral and industrial raw material resources of our country except for hard coal, coal and hydrocarbon resources in the best way and to make maximum contribution to the national economy by carrying out similar activities abroad and to carry out its activities in accordance with the principles of efficiency and profitability, is the leading company in the World boron sector.\n\nContact Kontrolmatik for more!\n', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\2VvSE3zvAGgEYyCwK1eF.png', 'kontrolmatik-eti-maden-75t-h-fluidized-bed-boiler', 'Kontrolmatik - ETİ Maden 75t / h Fluidized Bed Boiler', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-13 04:54:11', '2020-01-31 06:34:42', 'Kontrolmatik - ETİ Maden 75t / h Fluidized Bed Boiler', '[]', NULL, 'en', ''),
(30, 2, 6, 'dcs', 'Kontrolmatik - Türkerler Alaşehir JES-2 Automation and SCADA System', 'Kontrolmatik - Türkerler Alaşehir JES-2 Automation and SCADA System', 'Alasehir Turkey Jes-2 is Turkey\'s 16. biggest geothermal power plant with 24MW power. In this power plant, Kontrolmatik worked on controlling of the phases of geothermal resources from the production wells to the ', 'Alasehir Turkey Jes-2 is Turkey\'s 16. biggest geothermal power plant with 24MW power. In this power plant, Kontrolmatik worked on controlling of the phases of geothermal resources from the production wells to the turbine with the automation system and monitoring with the scada system.\n\nCUSTOMER PROFILE\nTürkerler is one of the leading companies in Turkey. It has Wind, Geothermal, Hydroelectric and Natural Gas Power Plants within the scope of energy sector.\n\nOBJECTIVE\n\nIt is aimed to control and follow up all processes including receiving from the geothermal water source production wells and automatic transfer to the turbine as steam at the desired pressure and flow rate, rather than the fuels used for the production of electricity. In addition, it is aimed to send the used resource back to underground via the reinjection system at the end of the cycle and to monitor the energy information used for internal and external needs and to perform energy equipment controls.\n\nRESULTS\nProduction is provided by monitoring the values belonging to well processes, reinjection system process, reinjection wells; monitoring of energy information and control of equipment through local control panels of each unit and these panels are communicated with central DCS-Scada system via fiber.\n\nCONTRIBUTION OF KONTROLMATİK\n\nAt the center of this system there are 2 redundant DCS CPUs and 2 redundant communication cards which enable these CPUs to communicate with related points.1 card works with the other 2 cpus in redundancy. At the same time, SCADA system has a redundant structure with 2 server PCs. In this way, the possibility of communication loss between the control center and the local control panels is minimized.\nIn the plant, 4 production well equipment are controlled fully automatically according to desired process values. Initiation and termination of the well process is done by automatic reactions of well head valves in order not to damage the wells.5 pieces of 1 MW pumps in 1 reinjection system operate in order to provide the desired reinjection pressure both by sequentially taking over and adjusting the set value. In addition to these, data from 5 reinjection wells and 1 compressor building can be monitored in order to send the source used in the system back to underground. Monitoring of energy information in all units; control and monitoring of equipment such as breaker, separator etc. can be done on the scada single line page of the lighting panels.\n\nHere, all system control and monitoring is independent of the central DCS. In particular, in case of problems in the fiber line for some reason in production well processes and reinjection process points in automatic production scenarios, in case of disconnection from the center, each unit continues the process by means of local controllers; in the points related to the purpose of monitoring and security of the process, it allows monitoring via pc panels at the relevant points and securing the control if necessary.\n', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\CCozB3e2TXKNUvuHX5wv.jpg', 'kontrolmatik-turkerler-alasehir-jes-2-automation-and-scada-system', 'Kontrolmatik - Türkerler Alaşehir JES-2 Automation and SCADA System', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-13 04:58:02', '2020-01-31 06:33:42', 'Kontrolmatik - Türkerler Alaşehir JES-2 Automation and SCADA System', '[]', NULL, 'en', ''),
