(37, 2, 13, 'industry-4.0', 'Internet of Things - An Overview', 'Internet of Things - An Overview', '\"Internet of Things\" is one of today\'s technology trends that we have begun to hear almost everywhere in the field of infor', '\"Internet of Things\" is one of today\'s technology trends that we have begun to hear almost everywhere in the field of information technologies (IT) and operational technologies (OT). It sometimes appears as Industry 4.0, sometimes as Industrial IoT (IIoT) and time to time as Internet of Things (IoT) in general. What makes this internet of things so valuable? And will it give us the future it promised? Else will it turn into another form and disappear, or will we not get the promises we expected?\nThese are not yet fully answered questions. In this article we will give a brief information about why the Internet of Things is valuable, how it can be done, the problems ahead of it and where to start. In our next articles we will examine them one by one.\nWhy? \nA brief look at history:\nIndustry 1.0: Steam Machines Industry 2.0: Mass Production Assembly Line Industry 3.0: Automation-Oriented Production Industry 4.0: Integration of Physical and Digital Systems With the beginning of the Industrial Revolution, manpower started to be replaced by machine power. With the invention of steam engines, the industrial revolution, which we now call Industry 1.0, begun.\nWith the subsequent serial production lines and then the development of computer-aided automation systems, we have automation systems that are still running today and working almost perfectly.\nNowadays we are talking about the combination of physical and digital worlds, the Internet of Things.\nThe first value that will be created by the Internet of Things is hidden in the Data. Interpreted data from our connected devices creates a chance to make more accurate decisions. In the next 5 years, a minimum of 25 billion new devices are expected to be connected to internet and to produce about 50 zettabytes of data.\nEmbedded intelligence ensures that all independent devices and data-generating points are visible and revelation of hidden correlations between them, making invisible patterns visible. (such as predictive maintenance)\nIncreased operational efficiency is provided through actionable predictions.Today, a typical oil extraction plant has an average of 30,000 data generating points, with only 1% of this data being available to decision-makers. In addition, no matter how advanced the technology and analysis techniques are, the top managements still make emotional and predictive decisions rather than analytical data. Therefore, it is inevitable that there will be social and organizational developments.\nEconomy of 1%:\nAccording to a survey conducted by GE, as seen in the figure; the economic value that can arise if corporations are able to operate 1% more efficiently than the current situation is quite high.\nIn addition, some of the potentials that can generate business value include:\nIncreased Revenue through New Products or Services Optimized operation Employee and Working efficiency Minimized business risks Savings from operational expenses Maintenance optimization How?\nIntranet or Internet?\nThe facilities we currently have provide an almost perfect level of operation thanks to advanced automation technologies. However, the information generated on the site is generally available only on site. Like an intranet network. The real value of the Internet of Things lies in the fact that this data can be used and interpreted together with the data of other devices and facilities, just like the internet network. Imagine a world where all facilities and even devices can communicate with each other! Today, when we say \"what is the internet?\", we think of concepts like search engines, social media, e-commerce; nobody mentions servers, network switches or routers. Who, or what, will be the new world\'s Google, Facebook, Twitter? We don\'t know that right now, and here lies the great potential.\nData Analysis\nData analysis is one of the most important points on the Internet of Things. With the interpretation of the data obtained from the machines by means of various analysis techniques and use of mathematical algorithms, previous useful information obtained from these data come to light. These information are sometimes used to identify problems on our systems, and sometimes to interfere before our devices break down, such as predictive maintenance.\nProblems\nAccess: The machines\' access to each other and to the platforms are needed to be delivered in an accessible, useable and reliable way, through either terrestrial or wireless technologies. Cyber Security: Along with new access and communication technologies, new types of cyber attacks are also developing. It is essential to take necessary precautions against the attacks that can be done through the objects. Integration of Data and Organizational Verticals: Communication of the teams within the organization is quite important for the potential of the internet of things to emerge. It is very important that the teams who unveil the data, convert the used data into application, support and use the application that will emerge to act jointly. Managing and revealing the value of big data: Solutions for the 4V (Velocity, Volume, Variety, Veracity) problem of big data should be created; it should be possible to handle the speed of the data, to store the data, to preserve its variety and to ensure its reliability; the analysis applications and algorithms used should be tracked carefully. Creation or support of expert staff or having a backup support plan: It should be possible to create a team capable of providing a wide range of support from the data scientist to the operating system specialist, or to have backup supporting options. Will there be unemployment? Will machines replace people? This question is being repeatedly asked in different courses. In retrospect, every industrial revolution creates its own business potential and generally reduces unemployment figures. But it also expects the employee to adapt to the new technologies and systems brought by the industrial revolution. As a result;\nCorrect integration is essential for an End-to-End solution. Cyber Security is indispensable. Organizational digitization and digital literacy are inevitable. The communication between verticals should be healthy and meet in one focus. Data should be available, more valuable than ever. Where to Start?\nEconomy of idea and data is coming, be prepared for it. Listen to your customers, consider their expectations and the change in the market. Act according to the desired business outcomes for your organization. Draw your road map for digitization, Big Data and the Internet of Things. Make innovation spread. Review your assets that produce Valuable Data. Make sure you get enough efficiency from your assets. Start with the right team or partner. Kontrolmatik IoT Services: Consulting: Industry 4.0, Industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) and Internet of Things (IoT) consulting and analysis services. Application Development: Dashboards, Web Pages, Mobile and Web Applications according to your monitoring needs for IoT. IoT Software and Hardware: We work as a partner with the world\'s leading companies in IT and OT fields. System Integration: We have been performing system integration projects as IT and OT for years. Field Services: We provide on-site support for data collection and installation services.\n \n', NULL, 'internet-of-things-an-overviews', 'Internet of Things - An Overview', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-13 05:27:15', '2020-01-31 09:08:36', 'Internet of Things - An Overview', '[]', NULL, 'en', '[]'),
