(42, 1, 16, 'mobile-substation', 'Mobile Substation', 'Mobile Substation', 'As the name implies, Mobile Substation is a substation on wheels. This System is used when a temporary power supplies are', 'As the name implies, Mobile Substation is a substation on wheels. This System is used when a\ntemporary power supplies are needed. Provides easy and flexible solutions.\n\nA mobile substation is a completely self-contained trailer mounted unit comprised of transformer, cooling equipment, high and low voltage circuit protection, metering, relaying, AC and DC auxiliary power supplies and surge protection.\n\nThe mobile substation is intended to be pulled by a truck tractor and for that reason is mounted on a specially designed semi-trailer chassis. Design and installation of a mobile substation have specific restrictions which are not present when designing conventional substations\n\nD.O.T. restrictions due to transport such as;\n\nLimiting dimensions and weights\nRoad regulations\nElectrical clearances\nApplications of Mobile Substation:\n\n\n\nContinuity of service for planned construction, maintenance and inspection programs\nStandby or temporary service\nOver-capacity service\nReplace complete substation in event of equipment failure\nElectrical power source in isolated areas\nBackup unit in countries with earthquake, flood, war, etc\nPower source for de-icing of HV lines in very cold areas\nIn case of emergency when urgent power supply is required\nIn military camps\nFeatures:\n\nAdvantages of Mobile Substation\n\nMobility in service\nQuick access for service\nLess Maintenance cost\nMinimum Clearance for utilization\nIncrease in Reliability\nMaximum KVA with minimum height.\n\n\nTypes Of Mobile Substations\n\n132/33kV (up to 60 MVA)\n132/11kV (16-35 MVA)\n33/11kV (5-16 MVA)\nSpecial design features can be implemented according to the requirements and specifications of the clients.\n\nMajor Components\n\nThere are five major components of a mobile substation:\n\n\n\nHigh Voltage Section\nTransformer and Cooling\nLow Voltage Section\nControls / Protection / Metering / Auxiliary Supply\nTrailer – special design features\nAs KONTROLMATİK we provide the followings;\n\nDesign of mobile substation including protection system.\nMounting,Test and Commissioning\nIsolating and Earthing Blade\n132 kV,SF6 Type,Outdoor C.B\nSurge Arrester\nMain Transformer-25 MVA\nAux. Grounding Transformer\nIsolating and Earthing Blade\nSwitchgears\nTrailer\nDual Battery Charger\nPanels\nSupply of electrical equipment/material/systems and trailer\nWhy Kontrolmatik?\n\nFast Installation Time\nCombining different projects causes a price advantage\nAfter sale services – at site and online\nHigh know-how and integrity\nContact Kontrolmatik for references.', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\IZp7fWc3xopD8qNksFTj.png', 'mobile-substation', 'Mobile Substation', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-13 05:53:08', '2019-09-13 05:53:08', 'Mobile Substation', '[\"Mobile Substation\"]', NULL, 'en', ''),
(43, 2, 23, 'scada', 'Kontrolmatik - AYEN Enerji Fangut HEPP', 'Kontrolmatik - AYEN Enerji Fangut HEPP', 'Ayen Enerji added a new one to its power plants. Fangut HEPP, established on the Fan River in Albania, was commissioned with the cooperation of Kontrolmatik-Small Hydro-GE.', 'Ayen Enerji added a new one to its power plants. Fangut HEPP, established on the Fan River in Albania, was commissioned with the cooperation of Kontrolmatik-Small Hydro-GE.\r\nCustomer Profile,\r\nThis is a company that establishes and operates renewable energy power plants which is especially active in Turkey and the Balkans.\r\nIt incorporates 10 power plants with a total capacity up to 500mW.\r\nObjective,\r\nPower plant with high reliability and efficiency. Managing and monitoring the entire system with the ABB 800xA Compact HMI from a single point. Controlling the whole plant and auxiliary systems under the same roof by combining 4 different control units under a single SCADA platform. Results,\r\nManaging and monitoring the entire system from a single control platform is provided. A system that can perform historical performance analysis was established by storing and graphical monitoring instant and historical data. Medium voltage protection relay configurations and tests were performed. Bassler Decs-100 panel is produced and commissioned for generator warning system.\r\nAdvantages of Kontrolmatik,\r\nKontrolmatik is a company that has commissioned many power plants and has a lot of experience in energy production. Our company is the solution partner of ABB and many companies producing industrial technology. Kontrolmatik is a company that has proven its ability to design and implement SCADA systems with their complete infrastructure.\r\nAbout Ayen A.S.\r\nIt is an energy company established in order to undertake tasks in the new energy investments to be made in our country and to complete the task successfully and to turn natural and renewable resources into energy and to bring them to the national economy.\r\nContact Kontrolmatik for more!', 'blog_posts/February2021/HnkPBzGyr0WOlPE5cIj6.jpg', 'kontrolmatik-ayen-enerji-fangut-hepp', 'Kontrolmatik - AYEN Enerji Fangut HEPP', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-13 06:10:57', '2021-02-27 08:03:39', 'Kontrolmatik - AYEN Enerji Fangut HEPP', '[]', NULL, 'en', '[]'),
(151, 2, 10, 'firewall', 'Reduce OT Cyber Threat Risk with ICS Network Visualization and Asset Inventory', 'Reduce OT Cyber Threat Risk with ICS Network Visualization and Asset Inventory', 'Convergence of information technologies (IT) and operational technologies (OT), OT being more connected to external networks, and the spread of industrial IoT devices help to increase the efficiency of industrial processes. However, these trends bring risks and security gaps. This causes institutions to feel insecure. ', 'Convergence of information technologies (IT) and operational technologies (OT), OT being more connected to external networks, and the spread of industrial IoT devices help to increase the efficiency of industrial processes. However, these trends bring risks and security gaps. This causes institutions to feel insecure. 77% of companies believe they may be the target of a cyber security case related to industrial control systems.\r\n\r\nIt is clear that industrial cyber threats are the most important concern for managers. CISO (Chief Information Security Officers) are looking for ways to assess and manage risks within the OT. But in fact, CISO staff does not have enough data to overcome cyber security and operational risks of ICS (Industrial Control System).  \r\nIn order to assess and manage risks, it is necessary to know when and how the cyber security network, assets and businesses are changing. Until recently, the tools available to easily visualize and document the industrial network were scarce and inaccessible.\r\n\r\nNozomi Networks, with SCADAguardian , offers industrial network monitoring technology that enables you to monitor your networks in real time in a completely passive manner and overcome the challenges posed by current asset inventories. \r\n\r\nNetwork Visualization Increases Situational Awareness and Resolution Speed\r\nPassive industrial network monitoring tools work by connecting to a SPAN or mirror port of a switch or router and analysing the communication within the network. In this sense, SCADAguardian offers an easy-to-implement integration solution that eliminates process risk.\r\nWhen the installation is complete, SCADAguardian starts analyzing the ICS network traffic and creates an interactive visualization. We are confident that a comprehensive system visibility at this level will change the minds of managers about OT management risk. When operators and cyber security personnel begin to analyse the system, they often realize that there are network nodes or IP addresses in system which they are not aware of.\r\n\r\nWith SCADAguardian, you can quickly access a large amount of useful information, \r\n\r\n	Macro view of an industrial control network including all assets and end points having IP or MAC address, communicating on the network,\r\n	Devices that do not have an IP address communicating on layer 2 of the OSI model,\r\n	Subnets, protocols used to communicate between subnets, and network topologies of VLANs,\r\n	Nodes and protocols used to communicate between these nodes,\r\n	Map of all network connections including session and connections,\r\n	Ability to view any end point or connection to see detailed attributes,\r\n	Network traffic information such as workflow, protocols, and open TCP connections,\r\n	Printable and openable versions of network structure and details in multiple file formats.\r\n\r\nNode topology visualization within the network, provided by SCADAguardian.\r\n\r\nA Quick and Easy Way to Inventory Your ICS \r\nDeveloping and maintaining a central OT system inventory is a very difficult and time-consuming project. Another key security solution provided by SCADAguardian is automated asset inventory.\r\nCustom asset views facilitate visualization, finding and elaboration of asset information. SCADAguardian has 3 different functional visualization options.\r\n\r\nThese are;\r\n\r\nVisual grouping based on the Purdue model, list view and detailed, single asset views.\r\nWhile SCADAguardian lists common industrial devices, it also shows detailed information such as device name, type, serial number, product software version, product name and components of the devices it lists. SCADAguardian keeps this information up-to-date by identifying their assets in a non-intrusive way and updates them in real time.\r\n\r\nSCADAguardian also captures contexts such as how each device is being used. For example, it notices that a Cisco key (as indicated by its MAC address) is used as a Siemens Scalence Key (PROD vendor). This important feature leads to lower faulty warnings in abnormality detection and security gap identification compared to products that recognize coverage systems. Changes in hardware, software and devices are sent via warnings to bring potential cyber events or process risks to the attention of appropriate personnel.\r\n\r\nNozomi Networks solution provides complete visibility of OT networks together with risk causes. Network visualization panels and automated asset inventory provide the basic information needed to accurately identify and correct ICS cyber security risks.\r\n\r\n** SCADAguardian ** also combines information from many industrial areas into a single monitoring toolkit and provides a common platform to facilitate IT / OT convergence.\r\nIf you are concerned about the risk of OT cyber attacks, contact us to learn how SCADAguardian improves your organization\'s operational visibility, how it can reduce cyber risks and improve reliability. (mail link)\r\n', 'blog_posts\\September2019\\2176ZoiRDDdNv1x54ShQ.jpg', 'reduce-ot-cyber-threat-risk-with-ics-network-visualization-and-asset-inventorys', 'Reduce OT Cyber Threat Risk with ICS Network Visualization and Asset Inventory', 'DRAFT', '0', '2019-09-12 09:24:02', '2020-01-31 06:49:31', 'Reduce OT Cyber Threat Risk with ICS Network Visualization and Asset Inventory', '[]', NULL, 'en', '');
