(29, 8, 3, 'Kenya-Gitaru HEPP Hydro Power Plant Rehabilitation Project', 'Kenya-Gitaru HEPP Rehabilitation Project', 'Kenya', '**Installed capacity		        : 2 x 72.5MW +  1 x 80.25MW**  \r\n\r\n**Generator voltage         	: 15kV**\r\n\r\n**Head	                                  : 141m**\r\n\r\n**Gitaru Power Plant is the largest power plant in Kenya covering %10  Energy needs of all Country and the biggest hydro power station in East Africa in terms of installed capacity**; it has three (3) Francis türbine.\r\n\r\nTwo vertical Francis turbines drive generators rated at 85MVA each at a net head of 135m. The power produced is transmitted to Kamburu 132kV substation, via two 132kV circuits and the station is remotely controlled from Kamburu. The third unit produces 80MW at 15kV that is stepped up to 220kV and is fed into the national grid at the Kamburu 220kV substation. The water is then passed on to Kindaruma, the oldest power station in the complex via an underground 4.7km long tailrace tunnel.\r\n\r\nThe control system in Gitaru is composed of two systems; automation PLC and the manual control system realized through relay logic. Manual control system has all requisite operator commands to the field devices via use of push buttons allowing control of all field equipment: - governor, pumps, excitation etc. All alarms and trip functions are wired individually to this system, but alarm facia is grouped for each system. The automation PLC receives status, alarm & trips signal from all field equipment and its able to send commands to all field equipment. A selector switch Manual /auto is used to interlock the two control systems.  The commands sent from the PLC go to the field devices via the robust relays in the manual control system. The units are normally operated in auto mode by the PLC; PLC’s are interconnected to KenGen SCADA system. Operator monitoring, and commands are carried out from a remote-control centre.  \r\n\r\n**PROJECT PURPOSE**\r\n\r\nIn order to improve power plant operations, KenGen has decided to rehabilitate the Protection and some station low voltage distribution boards. KenGen also intends to install new generator switchgear for units 2 & 3 to allow synchronization at 15KV and independent operation of the GSU transformer. \r\n\r\nThe project scope covers: studying of existing systems; design, Manufacture, Testing and training at the Manufacturer’s Factory; shipping & delivery to site (DAP); removal of existing equipment, Erection, Site Testing and Commissioning; generator MV switchgear, LV switchboards and protection systems of Gitaru hydro power station in Kenya. \r\n\r\n**PROJECT SCOPE**\r\n\r\nThe scope of works shall cover the following plant subsystems for Gitaru Hydro Power Plant: \r\n(a) Unit 2&3 MV generator switch gear, \r\n(b) Unit 2&3 protection  \r\n(c) Station LV switchboard- main station auxiliaries’ switchboard \r\n(d) Unit 1 station transformer installation \r\n(e) SCADA/communication interface equipment scope \r\n\r\n**DETAILED SCOPE OF SUPPLY**\r\n\r\n**1.	GENERATOR MV SWITCH GEAR SCOPE OF SUPPLY**\r\n\r\n* 	Generator Circuit breaker (GCB) cubicle for Unit II and Unit III (contain the withdrawable 5000A,17.5KV vacuum circuit breaker)\r\n* 	Station Transformer feeder & GSU transformer interface (Bus Riser) cubicle\r\n* 	Walk in Switchgear enclosure/Housing\r\n* 	Generator MV switchgear spare parts\r\n\r\n**2.	PROTECTION & SCADA SCOPE OF SUPPLY**\r\n\r\n* 	Generator Protection Panel\r\n* 	GSU transformer & station transformer protection Panel\r\n* 	Station   transformer   1,   Alternative   supply   transformer   and Emergency diesel generator Protection Panel\r\n* 	Protection System communication(SAS) Cabinet\r\n* 	Alarm Server Cabinet\r\n* 	Protection system spare parts\r\n\r\n**3.	LV SWITCHBOARDS SCOPE OF SUPPLY**\r\n\r\n* 	Main Station auxiliaries’ switchboards\r\n* 	Street & Flood lighting 4 Way TPN distribution board\r\n* 	Dewatering pumps turbine level maintenance cabinets\r\n* 	Control room Protection & Switchgear DC distribution board\r\n* 	Control room Emergency DC lighting distribution board\r\n* 	Power house Emergency DC lighting distribution board\r\n* 	LV switchboard spares\r\n\r\n**4.	CABLES AND ACCESSORIES SCOPE OF SUPPLY**\r\n\r\n* 	MV Cabling and Solid Insulated Bus Bars\r\n* 	LV Power Cables\r\n* 	Control & Auxiliary power supplies cables\r\n\r\n**5.	SERVICES**\r\n\r\n**	Engineering services **\r\n	\r\n(i)	Studying existing systems (study the existing Protection equipment, LV switch boards, generators, transformers, unit control systems, SCADA system and substation and all other associated plant systems to determine the interface and requirements of the new equipment\r\n(ii)	Power System Analysis Studies (Short-circuit studies , Generator Stability studies, Cable ampacity studies , Protection Coordination studies, DC auxiliary power system analysis)\r\n\r\n(iii)	Design (Software Configuration Management methodology, Arrangement (location) drawings of all equipment and all panel layout drawings showing component installation position and detailed dimensions, Detailed single line diagrams for all the systems, Block diagrams of the control philosophy for the control systems, List of inputs and outputs of all types (analogue & digital) for all IEDs, PLC’s and other software configurable devices. This list shall contain register/memory addresses and size/type of variables.)\r\n\r\n* Factory acceptance testing \r\n* Installation and commissioning services for Phase-I (Unit-2), Phase-II (Unit-3) and Phase-III (Common) \r\n* Factory training \r\n* On job training:\r\n    (i)	pre-installation and\r\n    (ii)	pre-SAT(Site Acceptance Test)  training \r\n* Site training -post commissioning\r\n* Technical documentation \r\n* Erection/Installation \r\n* Civil works that may be necessary during site works \r\n\r\n**6.	MAINTENANCE EQUIPMENT AND TOOLS**\r\n\r\n**7.	SOFTWARES SCOPE OF SUPPLY**\r\n\r\n* Design and computer licenses such as AutoCaD, Power System Analaysis, Microsoft windows and more\r\n* Protection System Licences such as Protection IED configuration (programming) manager, IEC61850 substation configuration manager, IEC61850 gateway VMware® software and more.\r\n* Alarm and events management system softwares licences\r\n* LV switchboard devices licences like switchboard PLC configuration (IEC61131-3 programming) manager licence and more', 'Kenya', 'Control , Protection, Rehabilitation, Generator Circuit Breaker, E House', 'posts/May2020/80opjrE5G0rJaYjG20GC.JPG', '[\"posts\\/May2020\\/IhOLznC0LISkpsYigCLN.jpg\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/S25pcxK5XBWYm059eIiB.JPG\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/Witnce0Ey3tz5GTPD7yU.JPG\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/nD1DKrRwEo8QiE7eyVxP.JPG\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/Z7enF5z5jBGCdDnq6ZbW.JPG\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/IQCitjk5SFTr4Yo1XVy7.JPG\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/lQ0BNPegkpU8nBKyM5QZ.jpg\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/UxIVd3AlUoyNAzW5kXBG.JPG\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/OoPJ4ss8HfhSgIipkGGO.JPG\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/Uob0u85wwbWOz9rv0fIW.JPG\",\"posts\\/May2020\\/hAabUc1VWfQ1EEu2W1lB.jpg\"]', 'posts/May2020/3IazqUMJ39s21Rqd38KF.jpg', 'kenya-gitaru-hepp-hydro-power-plant-rehabilitation-project', 'Kenya-Gitaru HEPP Rehabilitation Project', 'Kenya-Gitaru HEPP Rehabilitation Project, High Voltage, Low Voltage Panel, Generator Protection, Scada, automation, rehabilitation, hydroelectric power plant', 'PUBLISHED', 0, '2019-08-16 07:50:52', '2020-05-07 16:19:46', 21, 'en'),
