(43, 8, 3, 'Ethiopia Omo Kurnaz  Sugar Factory Electrical Panels Supply, Electrical Works and Engineering Services', 'Ethiopia Omo Kurnaz  Sugar Factory Electrical Panels Supply, Electrical Works and Engineering Services', 'Ethiopia', '**PROJECT PURPOSE**\r\n\r\nIt was in 2010 when Ethiopia starts the First Growth and Transformation (GTP I) that it set the ambitious plan of giving a significant boost to the sugar industry, hence placing it among the pillars of the overall economic transformation. Between 2010 and 2016, using the loans it secured and other sources, the government allotted close to 3.6 billion USD to expand the sugar industry, according to the 2016 Bloomberg report. By making the country to rank among the top-10 global producers by 2023, Ethiopian Sugar Corporation (ESC) plans to make the sugar industry a globally competitive one.\r\n\r\nOmo Kuraz Sugar Factory One is found in South region of South Omo Zone in Selamago District at a distance of 863 km from Addis Ababa.\r\n\r\nOmo Kuraz Sugar Factory was one of the first sugar factories that Ethiopia constructed.\r\n\r\n\r\n**PROJECT SCOPE**\r\n\r\n* Supply of Motor Control Cabinets (MCC) and Power Control Cabinet (PCC) equipment, including enclosures, spare parts & maintenance and installation tools according to list in annex.\r\n* Assembly of panels were done in Kontrolmatik workshop in Turkey.\r\n* Supervision for site installation of MCC & PCC panels at sugar factory in Ethiopia\r\n* Interfacing, testing & commissioning both at factory & site\r\n* Design of MCC & PCC layout of components\r\n* Design &  manufacturing drawing for enclosures\r\n* Submission of: Erection & installation methodology documents, operational manuals, maintenance manuals, catalogues and certificates.\r\n* Training', 'Ethiopia', NULL, 'posts\\August2019\\AaROXG6UfVf0qJ6EDWcc.jpg', '[\"posts\\\\August2019\\\\qOIFBprvamTWrRS9IujW.jpg\",\"posts\\\\August2019\\\\M1wgrc2l8zToTtzUTNOh.jpg\",\"posts\\\\August2019\\\\bGjgi2Bkee9Lwps3